---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Roughcut Stdio | Local-First Review Workflow for Editors"
  description="Roughcut Stdio is a local-first macOS desktop app that screens footage, surfaces strong candidate moments, and assembles a first-pass rough timeline for editorial review."
>
  <header class="page-shell">
    <div class="glass-panel sticky top-4 z-20 flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-[28px] px-4 py-4 md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between md:px-5">
      <a class="flex w-fit items-center gap-3" href="#top" aria-label="Roughcut Stdio home">
        <img src="/logo.svg" alt="" class="h-10 w-10 rounded-xl" width="1024" height="1024" />
        <span class="text-base font-bold tracking-[0.02em] text-rough-text">Roughcut Stdio</span>
      </a>
      <nav class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-4 gap-y-2 text-sm text-rough-muted" aria-label="Primary">
        <a class="nav-link" href="#features">Outcomes</a>
        <a class="nav-link" href="#workflow">Workflow</a>
        <a class="nav-link" href="#proof">Proof</a>
        <a class="nav-link" href="/guide">Guide</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main id="main-content" class="page-shell space-y-6 pb-24 pt-4">
    <section id="top" class="section-anchor grid gap-8 py-8 lg:grid-cols-[0.88fr_minmax(0,1.12fr)] lg:items-center lg:gap-10 xl:gap-12">
      <div class="space-y-7 lg:pt-4">
        <div class="reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Local-first footage screening for editors</p>
          <h1 class="mt-3 max-w-[11ch] text-[clamp(2.9rem,6.8vw,5.2rem)] font-extrabold leading-[0.94] tracking-[-0.045em] text-rough-text">
            Find the parts of the footage worth your time.
          </h1>
          <p class="lead mt-5 max-w-[60ch]">
            Roughcut Stdio is a macOS desktop app that scans large media sets locally, refines candidate segments, grades the strongest moments, and assembles a first-pass rough timeline so editors do not have to scrub every clip from start to finish.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-7 flex flex-wrap gap-3.5">
            <a class="button-base button-primary" href="#workflow">See the Workflow</a>
            <a class="button-base button-secondary" href="/guide">Read the Product Guide</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="mt-7 flex flex-wrap gap-2.5" aria-label="Product signals">
            <li class="chip">macOS desktop app</li>
            <li class="chip">Local-first analysis</li>
            <li class="chip">Resolve-ready FCPXML export</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal relative">
        <div class="halo halo--mint"></div>
        <div class="halo halo--gold"></div>

        <div class="relative ml-auto max-w-[760px]" data-tilt-card>
          <div class="visual-card glass-panel overflow-hidden rounded-[30px]">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-2 border-b border-white/5 px-4 py-3">
              <div class="flex gap-2">
                <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-white/20"></span>
                <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-white/20"></span>
                <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-white/20"></span>
              </div>
              <span class="text-[0.7rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-rough-muted">Review Surface</span>
            </div>
            <img
              src="/app.png"
              alt="Roughcut Stdio desktop review interface showing selected footage, graded sections, and export controls"
              class="w-full rounded-b-[30px]"
              width="1475"
              height="1015"
            />
          </div>

          <div class="floating-note absolute -right-3 top-[84px] z-10 hidden w-[232px] lg:block">
            <strong>Review-first</strong>
            <span>Best takes, grades, provenance, and export status in one surface.</span>
          </div>

          <div class="floating-note absolute -left-5 bottom-[78px] z-10 hidden w-[220px] sm:block lg:block">
            <strong>4-phase pipeline</strong>
            <span>Discover, analyze, select, and assemble without hiding the context.</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-4 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-3">
          <article class="glass-panel rounded-[18px] p-4">
            <span class="detail-kicker">Signals</span>
            <p class="text-sm leading-6 text-rough-muted">Technical, semantic, and story cues stay visible when reviewing candidate moments.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="glass-panel rounded-[18px] p-4">
            <span class="detail-kicker">State</span>
            <p class="text-sm leading-6 text-rough-muted">Runtime readiness and optional assets are separated so recovery stays legible.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="glass-panel rounded-[18px] p-4">
            <span class="detail-kicker">Export</span>
            <p class="text-sm leading-6 text-rough-muted">The current review state is shaped for an editorial handoff instead of a demo-only flow.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-5">
        <span class="detail-kicker">Process</span>
        <strong class="block text-base text-rough-text">4 focused phases</strong>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-rough-muted">Media discovery, per-asset analysis, take selection, and timeline assembly turn raw footage into a usable shortlist.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-5">
        <span class="detail-kicker">Runtime</span>
        <strong class="block text-base text-rough-text">Packaged desktop stack</strong>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-rough-muted">The packaged app bundles Python, analyzer resources, and media tools so the core workflow stays local.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-5">
        <span class="detail-kicker">Output</span>
        <strong class="block text-base text-rough-text">Editor stays in control</strong>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-rough-muted">Review shortlisted segments, promote a best take per clip, and export the active timeline into DaVinci Resolve.</p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section id="proof" class="section-anchor grid gap-4 pt-2 xl:grid-cols-[0.88fr_minmax(0,1.12fr)] xl:items-start">
      <div class="reveal max-w-3xl">
        <p class="eyebrow">Built for the real bottleneck</p>
        <h2 class="section-heading mt-3">The job is to reduce viewing burden, not replace editing.</h2>
        <p class="lead mt-5">
          Roughcut Stdio exists for the point in post-production where there is too much footage to watch manually. It narrows the search space, surfaces likely keeps, and makes the first rough selection inspectable enough that the editor can decide what actually deserves time.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3 xl:grid-cols-1">
        <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
          <span class="detail-kicker">Transcript-aware</span>
          <strong class="block text-base text-rough-text">Speech support stays local when transcript runtime is available</strong>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-rough-muted">Local transcript extraction can inform segment refinement, speech-aware scoring, and review without turning the workflow into a cloud dependency.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
          <span class="detail-kicker">Review provenance</span>
          <strong class="block text-base text-rough-text">Segments stay explainable inside the desktop review surface</strong>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-rough-muted">The app preserves how a segment was formed, what signals supported it, and which take is currently active in the assembled timeline.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
          <span class="detail-kicker">Graceful fallback</span>
          <strong class="block text-base text-rough-text">Optional AI paths can degrade without killing the workflow</strong>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-rough-muted">Deterministic analysis still runs when optional assets are unavailable, and the packaged app can step down transcript, CLIP, or local-VLM features as needed.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="features" class="section-anchor pt-2">
      <div class="reveal mb-6 max-w-3xl">
        <p class="eyebrow">What the tool actually does</p>
        <h2 class="section-heading mt-3">Three ways Roughcut Stdio helps before the real edit starts.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
          <span class="text-sm font-bold tracking-[0.18em] text-rough-warn">01</span>
          <h3 class="mt-5 text-[1.32rem] font-bold text-rough-text">Screen large footage sets locally</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 leading-7 text-rough-muted">Media discovery, proxy matching, frame sampling, audio analysis, and seed-region building all happen on your machine.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
          <span class="text-sm font-bold tracking-[0.18em] text-rough-warn">02</span>
          <h3 class="mt-5 text-[1.32rem] font-bold text-rough-text">Grade and compare candidate moments</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 leading-7 text-rough-muted">Deterministic scoring, optional local AI analysis, and review provenance make it easier to understand why one segment is worth keeping over another.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
          <span class="text-sm font-bold tracking-[0.18em] text-rough-warn">03</span>
          <h3 class="mt-5 text-[1.32rem] font-bold text-rough-text">Assemble a first-pass rough timeline</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 leading-7 text-rough-muted">The result is not a finished edit. It is a stronger starting point with shortlisted shots, best-take control, and a Resolve-oriented export path.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="workflow" class="section-anchor pt-2">
      <div class="reveal mb-6 max-w-3xl">
        <p class="eyebrow">How it flows</p>
        <h2 class="section-heading mt-3">One path from footage folder to editorial review.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
        <article class="workflow-step reveal glass-panel relative min-h-[220px] overflow-hidden rounded-[22px] p-6">
          <div class="mb-[18px] inline-flex h-[42px] w-[42px] items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-rough-accent/15 font-extrabold text-rough-accent">1</div>
          <h3 class="text-[1.32rem] font-bold text-rough-text">Media discovery</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 leading-7 text-rough-muted">Select a media folder, discover supported video files, and match sources to proxies before deeper analysis begins.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="workflow-step reveal glass-panel relative min-h-[220px] overflow-hidden rounded-[22px] p-6">
          <div class="mb-[18px] inline-flex h-[42px] w-[42px] items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-rough-accent/15 font-extrabold text-rough-accent">2</div>
          <h3 class="text-[1.32rem] font-bold text-rough-text">Per-asset analysis</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 leading-7 text-rough-muted">Extract frame and audio signals, build seed regions, refine segment boundaries, and apply transcript-backed or local-AI analysis when available.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="workflow-step reveal glass-panel relative min-h-[220px] overflow-hidden rounded-[22px] p-6">
          <div class="mb-[18px] inline-flex h-[42px] w-[42px] items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-rough-accent/15 font-extrabold text-rough-accent">3</div>
          <h3 class="text-[1.32rem] font-bold text-rough-text">Take selection</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 leading-7 text-rough-muted">Score the candidate segments, narrow them to the strongest takes per asset, and preserve the reasoning behind each recommendation.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="workflow-step reveal glass-panel relative min-h-[220px] overflow-hidden rounded-[22px] p-6">
          <div class="mb-[18px] inline-flex h-[42px] w-[42px] items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-rough-accent/15 font-extrabold text-rough-accent">4</div>
          <h3 class="text-[1.32rem] font-bold text-rough-text">Timeline assembly</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 leading-7 text-rough-muted">Preview the assembled timeline, promote or clear the best take for each clip, and export the active review state into Resolve via FCPXML.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section-anchor pt-2">
      <div class="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-[1.02fr_minmax(0,0.98fr)] lg:items-start">
        <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[28px] p-7">
          <p class="eyebrow">Inside the desktop app</p>
          <h2 class="section-heading mt-3 max-w-[14ch]">The review surface is built for selection, not spectacle.</h2>
          <p class="mt-5 leading-7 text-rough-muted">
            Roughcut Stdio shows shortlisted segments, transcript excerpts when available, grading signals, segment provenance, and the assembled timeline preview in one place so the editor can refine the first pass instead of reverse-engineering it.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-7 flex flex-wrap gap-3.5">
            <a class="button-base button-primary" href="/guide#desktop">See Desktop Details</a>
            <a class="button-base button-secondary" href="/guide#setup">Open Setup Steps</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
            <span class="detail-kicker">Best-take control</span>
            <p class="text-sm leading-6 text-rough-muted">The desktop review flow persists best-take overrides per clip so the exported timeline reflects the editor’s current decisions instead of a fixed auto-pick.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
            <span class="detail-kicker">Resolve handoff</span>
            <p class="text-sm leading-6 text-rough-muted">Export writes an FCPXML timeline that follows the active desktop review state so the next step can happen inside DaVinci Resolve, not in the browser.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="cta" class="section-anchor reveal pt-2">
      <div class="glass-panel relative overflow-hidden rounded-[30px] px-7 py-10 md:px-10">
        <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_top_right,rgba(95,209,166,0.2),transparent_32%),radial-gradient(circle_at_bottom_left,rgba(255,202,107,0.14),transparent_24%)]"></div>
        <div class="relative grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_auto] lg:items-end">
          <div>
            <p class="eyebrow">Next step</p>
            <h2 class="section-heading mt-3 max-w-4xl">Start with a media folder. Leave with a rough cut you can keep editing.</h2>
            <p class="lead mt-5 max-w-3xl">
              The product guide covers setup, the four-phase analyzer flow, packaged desktop runtime behavior, and how Roughcut Stdio hands work off to Resolve.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3.5">
            <a class="button-base button-primary" href="/guide#setup">Read Setup and Workflow</a>
            <a class="button-base button-secondary" href="/guide#desktop">See Desktop Runtime</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
